line_1: For what's content without a coach and six?" —
A Rev'rend Prelate stopt his Coach and Six,
line_2: To laugh a little at our Andrew's Tricks.

line_1: Not I, — for a coronet, chariot and six.'
line_2: His lying and filching, and Newgate-bird tricks: —

line_1: Nobly distinguish'd above all the six,
line_2: By deeds in which the world must never mix.

line_1: And give Humility a Coach and six?
line_2: Is Virtue's Prize: A better would you fix,

line_1: First went to dinner to my Lord's at six; —
line_2: But, as his friend had pleas'd the hour to fix,
Push'd thro' the Danube to the Shoars of Styx
